'''Corruption''' is both a [[financial]] issue, reducing the [[effectiveness of aid]] and [[development]] programs; it is also an abuse of [[power]].

[[Jeffrey Sachs]]{{w|Jeffrey Sachs}} claims that corruption is ''not'' the major problem facing Africa, citing examples of African countries that are ranked at the same level of corruption as countries in other regions, yet have much worse standards of growth, health etc.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/radio4/reith2007/lecture4.shtml Reith Lectures 2007 - Lecture 4: Economic Solidarity for a Crowded Planet] -  ''BBC Radio 4''.</ref>

